Description: Generates publication-ready summary tables for clinical research,
    supporting descriptive summaries and comparisons across two or three groups.
    Automatically detects whether each variable is continuous, binary, categorical,
    or ordinal and selects the appropriate statistical test (Welch t-test, Wilcoxon
    rank-sum, ANOVA, Kruskal-Wallis, Chi-squared, or Fisher's exact test). Results
    are formatted as tibbles and can be exported directly to Word or Excel with
    hierarchical category headers, publication-quality formatting, and an
    auto-generated statistical methods paragraph.
